---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'SafetyWing in Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-safetywing', text: 'Why SafetyWing for Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'limitations', text: 'Important Limitations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Who It\'s Best For', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Colombia', href: '/countries/colombia/insurance' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing vs IMG', href: '/compare/img-global-vs-safetywing' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price (Age 35)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Nomad Insurance', coverage: 'Travel medical', price: '$45-55/mo' },
  { plan: 'Remote Health', coverage: 'Comprehensive health', price: '$180-250/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing Health Insurance in Colombia"
  description="Guide to SafetyWing insurance for digital nomads in Colombia. Budget-friendly coverage designed for remote workers and nomads."
  headline="SafetyWing in Colombia"
  subheadline="Built for digital nomads. Budget-friendly coverage that meets Colombia visa requirements and travels with you."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/colombia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get SafetyWing"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/safetywing"
>
  <h2 id="overview">SafetyWing in Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing has become the default choice for digital nomads, and Colombia's thriving remote work scene makes it particularly relevant here. With extremely affordable pricing and a nomad-first approach, SafetyWing meets the needs of those who prioritize flexibility and value.
  </p>
  <p>
    The company was founded by nomads for nomads, and it shows in the product design—monthly subscription model, no fixed address required, coverage that works across borders.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$45-55</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Nomad Insurance)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Nomad-First</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Built for remote workers</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Visa Compliant</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Meets requirements</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get SafetyWing Coverage"
    description="Budget-friendly insurance for digital nomads in Colombia."
    buttonText="Get Covered"
    buttonHref="/providers/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-safetywing">Why SafetyWing for Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing is popular among Colombia's digital nomad community for good reasons:
  </p>

  <h3>Unbeatable Price</h3>
  <p>
    At $45-55/month for basic coverage, SafetyWing costs a fraction of traditional international health insurance. For young, healthy nomads, this makes comprehensive coverage financially accessible.
  </p>

  <h3>Nomad-Friendly Design</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Monthly subscription:</strong> No annual commitment required</li>
    <li><strong>No fixed address:</strong> Coverage follows you, not your location</li>
    <li><strong>Easy signup:</strong> Online in minutes</li>
    <li><strong>Simple cancellation:</strong> Stop anytime</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Meets Visa Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing is accepted for Colombia's digital nomad visa. The coverage certificate satisfies the insurance requirement for visa applications.
  </p>

  <h3>Colombia Context</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing works well in Colombia specifically because:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Local healthcare is affordable, reducing insurance dependency</li>
    <li>Large nomad community provides peer support and recommendations</li>
    <li>Major cities have quality hospitals for serious needs</li>
    <li>Low cost of living makes budget insurance sensible</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance (Travel Medical)</h3>
  <p>
    The flagship product at ~$45/month (age 10-39):
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>$250,000 maximum coverage</li>
    <li>$250 deductible</li>
    <li>Covers emergencies, hospitalization, some outpatient</li>
    <li>Travel coverage included (30 days home country)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Remote Health (Comprehensive)</h3>
  <p>
    Full health insurance at ~$180-250/month:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>$1,000,000+ coverage limits</li>
    <li>Routine care, preventive, and chronic conditions</li>
    <li>More comparable to traditional health insurance</li>
    <li>Higher cost but genuine comprehensive coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Which Plan?</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Nomad Insurance works for healthy young nomads who mostly need catastrophic coverage. Remote Health is appropriate if you want traditional health insurance with routine care coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance Covers</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Accidents, sudden illness, ER visits</li>
    <li><strong>Hospitalization:</strong> Inpatient care when medically necessary</li>
    <li><strong>Urgent care:</strong> Non-emergency urgent situations</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation if needed</li>
    <li><strong>Travel delay:</strong> Some trip interruption benefits</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Remote Health Adds</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Routine care:</strong> Annual checkups, GP visits</li>
    <li><strong>Preventive:</strong> Vaccinations, screenings</li>
    <li><strong>Chronic conditions:</strong> Ongoing management</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Therapy and psychiatric care</li>
    <li><strong>Prescriptions:</strong> Outpatient medications</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="limitations">Important Limitations</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing has trade-offs you should understand:
  </p>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Not comprehensive health insurance:</strong> Designed for emergencies, not routine care</li>
    <li><strong>Pre-existing conditions:</strong> Not covered</li>
    <li><strong>US coverage:</strong> Limited (30 days only, as travel)</li>
    <li><strong>Chronic conditions:</strong> Not covered under Nomad Insurance</li>
    <li><strong>Elective procedures:</strong> Not covered</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>General Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>No direct billing:</strong> Usually pay upfront, get reimbursed</li>
    <li><strong>Claims process:</strong> Can be slower than premium insurers</li>
    <li><strong>Customer service:</strong> More limited than Cigna/BUPA/Allianz</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Realistic Expectations</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is excellent for what it is: affordable catastrophic coverage. It's not a substitute for comprehensive health insurance. In Colombia, where routine care costs $30-60, paying out of pocket for minor issues while having SafetyWing for emergencies is a reasonable strategy for healthy young nomads.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="best-for">Who It's Best For</h2>

  <h3>Young Digital Nomads</h3>
  <p>
    Healthy 20-30 somethings who primarily need emergency coverage. The low cost and flexibility align perfectly with the nomad lifestyle.
  </p>

  <h3>Budget-Conscious Travelers</h3>
  <p>
    If comprehensive insurance isn't financially viable, SafetyWing provides meaningful protection at an accessible price point.
  </p>

  <h3>Short to Medium Stays</h3>
  <p>
    For 3-12 month stays in Colombia, SafetyWing's month-to-month approach avoids annual commitments.
  </p>

  <h3>Those Comfortable with Risk</h3>
  <p>
    If you're comfortable handling routine care out of pocket and treating SafetyWing as catastrophic coverage, it works well.
  </p>

  <h3>Not Ideal For</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Those with pre-existing conditions (consider IMG or Cigna)</li>
    <li>Expats wanting traditional comprehensive coverage (consider Allianz, BUPA)</li>
    <li>Anyone needing regular ongoing care</li>
    <li>Those uncomfortable with reimbursement model</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Get SafetyWing for Colombia"
    description="Affordable coverage for digital nomads."
    buttonText="Get Covered"
    buttonHref="/providers/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance, not traditional health insurance. Understand the coverage limitations before relying on it as your only protection.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
